The potent antifungal activity of CMEO was owed to
its chemical constituents such as geraniol, geranial, linalool,
isomenthol. These aromatic compounds cause permeabilization
of cellular membranes by destructing the lipids and proteins,
and brings coagulation of cytoplasm, leakage of ions, breakdown
of proton pump, drop in mitochondrial membrane potential
and reduction of ATP molecules, release of cytochrome c and
these concurrent events boost the death of fungi by apoptosis
